== Naruyamcha Gets /b/ ==
Due to the massive lulz that Naruyamcha drags around with him like a shit-soaked blanket, a member of #narutofan IRC channel impersonated him on /b/, with explosive, quasi-legendary results. These screen-shots were taken by the very person who performed this, influenced by several other members of the #narutofan IRC channel, and spread them through the channel quickly.

[http://img530.imageshack.us/img530/7695/mariocq8.png Naru /b/ Saga Part 1]

[http://img530.imageshack.us/img530/4227/mario2oz0.png Naru /b/ Saga Part 2]

[http://img514.imageshack.us/img514/6202/mario3tu9.png Naru /b/ Saga Part 3]

The thread in /b/ lasted three and a half hours and became, for a brief moment, epic in the NarutoFan Forums, where people would post topics on it and ask if it was the real Naru that was doing all of this. All attempts at clarification were crushed by the mods and admins of the forum, due to the whining complaints of Naru. After this event, Naru threatened several parties that were involved before claiming that the pictures were of his '''cousin''' and that he would '''wait in fear of being beaten to a bloody pulp'''.

[[Image:Negro-frowns.jpg|thumb|These Negros frown upon the shenanigans of Naruyamcha. Conveniently, the one that looks like Forest Whitaker is an Assistant District Attorney of the state of New York and will be the one prosecuting the case against him for endangering the welfare of a child, sexual harassment, attempt to commit child molestation, soliciting a child for sexual acts, and various other charges.]]


== Naruyamcha's Disappearance ==

Only minutes after the /b/ incident, Naru immediately began to place blame on everyone he once considered a friend, in spite of the fact that there were none that thought of him the same way. In a frenzy, he damned everyone and rushed from the IRC channel #narutofag, subsequently leaving #narutofan as well. This was shortly after he claimed that the pictures that were posted of him were actually of his '''cousin'''. He also stated that he was going to '''wait in fear until his cousin comes home and beats him to a bloody pulp'''. Several moments afterwards, he claimed he heard his cousin coming home and immediately logged off, only to return minutes later. Once again, he condemned everyone in the channel and left. He has not been seen on IRC since, and it was rumored that he had killed himself, however several people have spoken to him on the MSN Messenger service.


